article.headline: Detroit 80, Green Bay 73
article.story: GREEN BAY, Wis. -- Ray McCallum Jr. scored 16 points, Jason Calliste added 14 and Detroit rallied late for an 80-73 victory against Green Bay on Thursday night. A 3-pointer by Calliste and driving layup by McCallum keyed a game-ending 18-7 run for the Titans (9-10, 3-4 Horizon League). Alec Brown had 17 points and nine rebounds for the Phoenix (6-10, 2-4), who played a home game for the first time in three weeks. Brennan Cowgill added 13, Terry Johnson 11 and Kiefer Sykes 10. Doug Anderson and LaMarcus Lowe hit two free throws each to help Detroit knot the score at 66-all with 4:08 remaining. Calliste's 3-pointer broke the deadlock, and after two more free throws by Lowe, McCallum drove for his layup to make it 73-66 with 2:25 to play. The Titans protected the lead at the foul line. Lowe had 13 points and seven rebounds. Eli Holman scored 11 points for Detroit.
